LAGOS  – The police authorities have dis­missed an inspector who shot and killed a civilian during a stop and search operation in Delta State. The police also disclosed that the Inspector, Ubi Ebri , had been charged to court and remanded at Ogwashi-Uku Correctional Centre. Bright Edade, Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), Delta State Command, disclosed in a statement on Wednesday. Edade, a Deputy Superinten­dent of Police (DSP), said: “Following the murder of one Onyeka Ibe who was allegedly shot at by one Inspector Ubi Ebri attached to Area command patrol team, while on stop and search duty along Ugbolu-Illah road on April 5, 2023, the Com­mand wishes to inform mem­bers of the public as promised, that the said Inspector has been dismissed from the Nigeria Po­lice force after the conclusion of the orderly room trial at the state headquarters.” He said the dismissed inspec­tor was on Wednesday April 19,2023 arraigned before the Asaba magistrate’s court on a re­mand proceedings for the murder. The police image maker added that the court had ordered that the accused be remanded at the Ogwashi- Uku correctional cen­ter, while the case file be sent to the Director of Public Prosecu­tion (DPP) for legal advice and prosecution by the office of the DPP.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ “The command has therefore tasked officers and men to uphold the tenets of professional policing in the discharge of their duties with respect to fundamental hu­man rights of all citizens in line with the provisions of the 1999 constitution of the federal re­public of Nigeria (as amended), while hoping that this will serve as a deterrent to others officers.”